<doc id="700232" wikidata="Q836420" url="?curid=700232" title="Joseph Weber Award for Astronomical Instrumentation">
<text>The Joseph Weber Award for Astronomical Instrumentation is awarded by the American Astronomical Society to an individual for the design, invention or significant improvement of instrumentation leading to advances in astronomy. It is named after physicist Joseph Weber. The awards tend to be for a career of instrument development rather than a single specific device; the lists of inventions below are taken from press releases from the recipients&#x27; institutions.

==Weber Award winners==
Source: American Astronomical Society

